The Victoria Bridge will be lit Pink, Green, White, Light Blue and Yellow to celebrate FIFA Women&#39;s World Cup.

From 20 July to 20 August, Aotearoa/New Zealand and Australia will co-host the FIFA Women&rsquo;s World Cup. This will be the first time that the tournament will be co-hosted across two countries and Brisbane/Meaajin is proud to be one of the nine Host Cities.

As well as hosting matches, a Fan Festival&trade; in Brisbane/Meaanjin will take place at the South Bank Parklands, offering the perfect place to watch live FIFA Women&rsquo;s World Cup&trade; matches and enjoy an exciting program of music, entertainment, food and games.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Find out more at FIFA Women&rsquo;s World Cup Australia &amp; New Zealand 2023&trade;

This Light Up is organised by: Brisbane Economic Development Agency
